I’ve had a wild obsession with Drunken Noodles since Jr High - I can eat this every day and never get sick of it. Chili, garlic, basil... what more can you ask for? The noodles are perfectly chewy and soak up that delicious sauce, while the veggies have that desirable crunch. It’s absolute perfection. Find the measurements listed below ⬇️ Enjoy 💕 #spicednice ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Marinade:⁣⁣
🍗1 lb boneless chicken thigh, thinly sliced ⁣⁣
🍗2 tsp soy sauce⁣⁣
🍗2 tsp sesame oil ⁣⁣
🍗2 tsp cornstarch ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Sauce: ⁣⁣
🌶2 tsp brown sugar ⁣⁣
🌶2 tsp dark soy sauce ⁣⁣
🌶2 tsp light soy sauce ⁣⁣
🌶1 tsp hoisin sauce ⁣⁣
🌶1 tbsp fish sauce ⁣⁣
🌶2.5 tsp oyster sauce⁣⁣
🌶1/4 tsp white pepper ⁣⁣
🌶1 tsp chili paste or chili oil (optional 🌶)⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🧄3 tbsp vegetable oil ⁣⁣
🧄1 tbsp crushed garlic ⁣⁣
🧄1 tsp minced ginger ⁣⁣
🧄2 tsp finely diced red chili pepper (optional 🌶)⁣⁣
🧄1 large onion, cut into wedges ⁣⁣
🧄1 red bell pepper, cut into wedges ⁣⁣
🧄2 green onions, sliced into 2 inch pieces ⁣⁣
🧄1 cup Thai basil leaves⁣⁣
🧄3 Thai chilis (optional 🌶) ⁣⁣
🧄1, 10 Oz pack wide rice noodles⁣⁣
🧄1/2 cup baby corn

Want to spoil your loved ones or yourself? ❤️ These Stuffed Potatoes are simply a must. 🥔🤤 They’re stuffed with a flavorful meat mixture that is good enough to devour on its own and baked in a savory tomato sauce. Enjoy the recipe in the video and find the measurements and ingredients written below ⬇️⬇️ #spicednice #valentinesday ⁣
⁣
Ingredients: ⁣
🥔12 small/medium sized potatoes ⁣
🥔Oil for frying⁣
Beef filling:⁣
🥩1 lb ground beef ⁣
🥩1/2 cup Toasted pine nuts ⁣
🥩1 small onion, diced ⁣
🥩1/2 red bell pepper, finely diced ⁣
🥩1 tbsp of each: chopped parsley, oregano, & basil⁣
🥩1 tsp Allspice ⁣
🥩1/2 tsp Cumin ⁣
🥩1.5 tsp Seven spice ⁣
🥩1 tsp Coriander ⁣
🥩1.5 tsp Paprika ⁣
🥩optional: 1.5 tsp Chili powder ⁣
🥩Black pepper to taste⁣
🥩Salt to taste ⁣
Sauce:⁣
🍅2 cloves Garlic ⁣
🍅1 6oz can Tomato paste ⁣
🍅2.5 cups chicken broth (or water) ⁣
🍅Salt, pepper, allspice to taste

This Seafood Boil with Cajun Garlic Butter Sauce recipe serves as not only a delicious dinner, but also as a fun family activity! This can get messy so spread a table cover onto your dining table and have fun peeling the shrimp and dipping it into the heavenly butter sauce! Enjoy ❤️ #spicednice⁣
⁣
Ingredients: ⁣
⁣
Seafood Boil: ⁣
🦐6 lb jumbo, easy peel shrimp ⁣
🦐2 lb baby redskin potatoes ⁣
🦐12 pieces of cut corn on the cob ⁣
🦐7 cups chicken broth (or however much you need to fill your large pot) ⁣
🦐2 lemons, quartered ⁣
🦐1 onion, cut into large strips ⁣
🦐10 garlic cloves ⁣
🦐1 inch piece of ginger ⁣
🦐4 bay leaves ⁣
🦐3 tbsp old bay seasoning ⁣
🦐1 tbsp lemon pepper ⁣
🦐optional: 2 tbsp creole seasoning ⁣
🦐salt to taste, if needed ⁣
⁣
Cajun Garlic Butter Sauce:⁣
🧄5 sticks unsalted butter ⁣
🧄1/2 small onion ⁣
🧄15 cloves of garlic ⁣
🧄2 1 inch pieces of ginger ⁣
🧄2 tbsp Cajun seasoning ⁣
🧄1 tbsp garlic powder ⁣
🧄1 tbsp paprika ⁣
🧄1 tsp black pepper ⁣
🧄1 tbsp onion powder ⁣
🧄1 tbsp oregano ⁣
🧄1/2 tsp cayenne ⁣
🧄1 tbsp lemon pepper ⁣
🧄1 tbsp chili powder ⁣
🧄1 tbsp hot sauce of choice ⁣
🧄2-3 tbsp brown sugar (to taste) ⁣
🧄2 tsp Worcestershire sauce ⁣
⁣
🦐lemon wedges for serving

I partnered with @shepherdmeats to create this Barbacoa Taco recipe in my @instantpotofficial ! Feel free to use @shepherdmeats Chuck Roast (my usual go to for this recipe) instead of beef cheek. 😋 No matter which cut you choose, any meats from @shepherdmeats will blow you away. Head to their website (link in their bio) to purchase the most premium, tender, zabiha halal meat that DELIVERS to your doorstep! Do you guys want to see more videos like this?! RECIPE ⬇️ #spicednice⁣
🎥: @tarek.em ⁣
🌮4 lb @shepherdmeats Beef chuck roast or beef cheek⁣
🌮1/2 large Onion, quartered ⁣
🌮8 Garlic cloves ⁣
🌮2-4 Chipotle peppers (adjust to preferred spice level) ⁣
🌮3 tsp olive oil ⁣
🌮1.5 tbsp Adobo sauce ⁣
🌮1/3 cup Lime juice ⁣
🌮2 cups Beef broth ⁣
🌮1 tbsp Paprika ⁣
🌮3 tsp Smoked paprika ⁣
🌮2 tsp Ground cloves⁣
🌮1.5 tbsp Cumin ⁣
🌮2 tbsp Dried oregano ⁣
🌮2 tsp Black pepper ⁣
🌮1.5 tsp Brown sugar⁣
🌮1 tsp Onion powder ⁣
🌮1 tsp Garlic powder⁣
🌮3 Bay leaves⁣
🌮Salt to taste ⁣
⁣
1. In a blender, combine the onion, garlic, chipotle peppers, adobo sauce, lime juice, beef broth, paprika, smoked paprika, cumin, dried oregano, ground cloves, black pepper, brown sugar, and salt. Blend together until a smooth red sauce has formed. Adjust seasoning and salt to taste. ⁣
2. Season all sides of the chuck roast with salt, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, smoked paprika, cumin, and dried oregano. Set the Instant Pot to the sauté option. Drizzle in some olive oil and let that heat up, then sear the roast on each side for about 3-4 minutes or until browned. Add the blended sauce in as well as the bay leaves. Lock the lid on and set to the pressure cook setting on high for (2 lb roast for 50 minutes, 3 lb for 60 minutes, and 4 lb roast for 70 minutes) For stovetop cooking, bring to a simmer over medium heat, then set heat to low and simmer with the lid on for about 4.5 hours for a 4 lb roast. ⁣
3. Once the meat is done cooking, shred with two forks. Assemble the meat into corn tortillas and scoop out the sauce into a  bowl for dipping. Top the tacos with diced onions and cilantro and serve with the sauce and guacamole on the side. Enjoy!

Watermelon Mint Cooler 🍉🌴 The perfect EASY Summer drink! Who’s trying it out soon? 🙋🏻‍♀️ Find the written recipe below, enjoy! ⬇️⬇️ #spicednice ⁣
🍉5 cups FROZEN diced watermelon⁣
🍉1 handful mint leaves⁣
🍉2.5 tbsp lime juice ⁣
🍉3 tbsp sugar or to taste (can use honey or other sweetener)⁣
🍉1/4 cup crushed ice ⁣
🍉1/3 cup water (sprite, ginger ale, or carbonated water all work as well for a fun option!)⁣
⁣
1. Freeze the diced watermelon for at least a few hours. Then add the frozen watermelon to a blender along with the mint, lime juice, sugar or sweetener of choice, ice, and a splash of liquid. Blend just until smooth and serve! Enjoy🌴

Super Zesty Middle Eastern Potato Salad 🌱🍋🧄 I’m living for these easy and flavorful Summer Recipes and this one is a top favorite. The potatoes soak up the fresh herbs, garlic, lemon, and spices so beautifully. Enjoy the written recipe below ⬇️ #spicednice ⁣
⁣
🥔water for boiling ⁣
🥔salt, be sure to heavily salt the water so the insides of the potatoes aren’t bland! ⁣
🥔8 russet potatoes, peeled and diced into 1 inch cubes ⁣
🥔1.5 tbsp crushed garlic ⁣
🥔3 green onions, thinly sliced ⁣
🥔1/4 cup finely chopped fresh mint⁣
🥔1/2 bunch parsley, finely chopped ⁣
🥔1 tsp Aleppo pepper (can sub with 1 tsp red pepper flakes) ⁣
🥔1/4 tsp black pepper⁣
🥔1/2 tsp allspice ⁣
🥔1/2 tsp cumin⁣
🥔Salt to taste ⁣
🥔1/4 cup + 2 tbsp lemon juice ⁣
🥔1/4 cup olive oil ⁣
⁣
1. Heavily salt a pot of water then add your peeled and diced potatoes. Be sure to add the potatoes in while the water is cold so they cook evenly. Boil these until cooked through or for a quicker method, pressure cook in the instant pot for 3 minutes. Once they’re ready, strain them and set aside to cool. ⁣
2. In a large bowl, mix the garlic, green onions, mint, parsley, Aleppo pepper, black pepper, allspice, cumin, salt, lemon juice, and olive oil. Add in the cooked potatoes and mix until fully coated then serve. Enjoy!

Lets kick off the Summer recipes with my FAVORITE Chipotle Seven Layer Bean Dip! 🍅🥑 No exaggeration this may be my favorite dip recipe. It’s simple, but we flavor every layer over here and it makes all the difference! Enjoy 🥰 #spicednice ⁣
⁣
Beans: ⁣
🥑2 cups refried beans (16 Oz)⁣
🍅1/3 cup fire roasted diced tomatoes⁣
🥑1 finely chopped chipotle pepper⁣
🍅1 tsp adobo sauce ⁣
🥑1/2 tsp cumin⁣
🍅1/2 tsp chili powder ⁣
🥑1 tsp garlic powder⁣
🍅1/2 tsp onion powder⁣
🥑1/2 tsp salt⁣
Quick Guac: ⁣
🥑3 large avocados⁣
🥑juice of 1 lime (or to taste)⁣
🥑1 tsp crushed garlic⁣
🥑1 tbsp chopped cilantro⁣
🥑1/4 tsp black pepper⁣
🥑1/2 tsp salt ⁣
Other layers:⁣
🍅sour cream⁣
🍅your favorite salsa⁣
🍅shredded Mexican cheese⁣ blend
🍅sliced olives⁣
🍅sliced green onions ⁣
🍅chopped cilantro

What to do when you have bananas about to go bad and a kitty named Biscoff? Biscoff Banana Bread, of course 🥰🍌 This bread is SO moist and flavorful you won’t be able to stop at one slice! Find the written recipe below ⬇️ Enjoy! #spicednice ⁣
⁣
🍌1/2 cup unsalted butter (1 stick), softened ⁣
🍌3/4 cup brown sugar ⁣
🍌2 eggs at room temperature ⁣
🍌1/2 tsp vanilla extract ⁣
🍌3 ripe bananas (or 1 cup total mashed) ⁣
🍌2 cups all purpose flour ⁣
🍌1/2 tsp salt ⁣
🍌1 tsp baking soda ⁣
🍌1/2 tsp cinnamon ⁣
🍌1/4 cup sour cream ⁣
🍌1/2 cup cookie butter, microwaved for 15 seconds⁣
🍌2 tbsp melted cookie butter, for drizzling⁣
🍌OPTIONAL: chopped walnuts! ⁣
⁣
1. Preheat oven to 350°F. In a bowl, use a hand mixer to cream the softened butter and brown sugar together for about 3-4 minutes. Beat in the room temperature eggs, 1 at a time. Whip in the vanilla extract and mashed bananas until fully combined. ⁣
2. In a separate bowl, combine sifted flour, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon. Pour these dry ingredients into the wet banana batter and whisk until fully mixed in. Fold in the sour cream and melted cookie butter.⁣
3. Lightly grease a 9x5 baking dish and pour half of the batter in. Drizzle 1 tbsp of melted cookie butter on top and lightly swirl it into your batter, then pour the remaining half of the batter on top. Swirl in the remaining 1 tbsp cookie butter then bake for about 60 minutes or until an inserted toothpick in the center of the bread comes out clean.⁣
4. Let it cool for 10 minutes in the baking dish, then remove and allow it to cool for another 10 minutes on a cooling rack. Enjoy with some optional additional Biscoff spread! ❤️

Sweet and Smoky Drumsticks 🍗 Absolutely delicious and packed with so much flavor, especially for such a quick and easy meal 🙌🏼 Find the written recipe below, enjoy! #spicednice ⬇️⬇️⁣
⁣
🍗6 drumsticks ⁣
🍗1/4 cup honey ⁣
🍗2 tsp paprika ⁣
🍗2 tsp smoked paprika ⁣
🍗2 tbsp Cajun seasoning ⁣
🍗2 tsp chili powder ⁣
🍗2 tsp garlic powder ⁣
🍗1 tsp black pepper⁣
🍗1 tsp salt or to taste⁣
🍗3.5 tbsp avocado or vegetable oil ⁣
 ⁣
1. Mix all the ingredients in a bowl except for the chicken. Once you have a red paste, add in the drumsticks and score the chicken all over so the marinade flavors the chicken to the bone. If you have time, I recommend marinating for at least 30 minutes. ⁣
2. Spray the air fryer with nonstick cooking spray then place the drumsticks inside. Air fry at 380°F for 8 mins then flip and cook for another 12-15 minutes (flip every 5 mins). Depending on the size of your drumsticks and the air fryer being used (I’ve noticed different air fryers cook slightly differently) keep an eye on the drumsticks towards the end and cook until the internal temperature has reached 165°F. ⁣
3. Alternative BAKING INSTRUCTIONS: preheat oven to 400°F and bake for 35-40 mins or until internal temperature has reached 165°F. Flip once halfway through and enjoy!

Korean Rabokki (mix of Tteokbokki and Ramen) is probably one of the most satisfying & entertaining meals you can have with your friends and family. So many delicious and chewy textures in a rich red broth. 🍜🥟 It’s commonly eaten by gathering around the portable burner and eating directly from the boiling pan, so that’s how we enjoyed it today and it was such a fun experience! Find the written recipe below, enjoy ⬇️⬇️ #spiced ⁣
⁣
🍜5.5 cups of water (or use anchovy broth for a more authentic taste!) ⁣
🍜5.5 tbsp Korean chili paste (gochujang)⁣
🍜2 tbsp sugar ⁣
🍜1 tbsp minced garlic ⁣
🍜1 tbsp soy sauce⁣
🍜1 tsp chicken bouillon powder (this is optional as it’s not authentic but I loved the flavor it added!)⁣
🍜1.5 tsp Korean red chili flakes (gochugaru)⁣
🍜12 dumplings ⁣
🍜Handful of Extra wide rice noodles ⁣
🍜6.5 Oz Korean rice cakes (about 17 pieces)⁣
🍜1 instant noodle ramen pack⁣
🍜 2 scallions, thinly sliced⁣
🍜toasted sesame seeds for topping ⁣
Other common optional ingredients:⁣
🍜Fish cakes⁣
🍜Cabbage leaves ⁣
🍜Hard boiled eggs ⁣
🍜Cheese ⁣
⁣
1. Bring the water to a boil in a wide pan. Meanwhile, prep the sauce by mixing the Korean chili paste, sugar, garlic, soy sauce, bouillon powder, and Korean chili flakes in a bowl. It should create a bright red paste! ⁣
2. Once the water is boiling, add the sauce and stir it in until it dissolves. Once it starts to boil again, lower the heat to medium and add in all your noodles, rice cakes, dumplings, and any of the optional ingredients you wish to add. Allow everything to cook through then top with sliced scallions and toasted sesame seeds. Enjoy!

Mersin Patates - Crispy, Zesty Turkish style Potatoes. 🥔🍋 Safe to say I’m obsessed with these. The tangy flavors soak into the crispy potatoes so perfectly! Find the written recipe below, enjoy! #spicednice ⁣
⁣
Yogurt sauce: ⁣
🍋1 cup plain yogurt ⁣
🍋1/4 tsp salt or to taste ⁣
🍋1/2 tsp crushed garlic ⁣
🍋1 tbsp lemon juice⁣
Potatoes:⁣
🥔5 potatoes, sliced at about 1/8 of an inch⁣
🥔cold water for soaking⁣
🥔1 tbsp vinegar ⁣
🥔Salt to taste ⁣
🥔Oil for frying ⁣
🥔Squeeze of Lemon juice ⁣
🥔Sprinkle of sumac ⁣
🥔Parsley for garnish ⁣
⁣
1. Mix the ingredients for the yogurt sauce and set aside in the refrigerator. Peel and slice your potatoes into 1/8 inch slices. You can definitely use a mandolin here if you prefer! Cover the potatoes in cold water and 1 tbsp vinegar. Allow this to soak for 1 hour, then strain the potatoes and season with salt. ⁣
2. Heat up the frying oil then fry the potatoes until golden and crispy. Strain out any excess oil then transfer to your serving plate. Squeeze on lemon juice, add a generous sprinkle of sumac, and chopped parsley. Serve with the garlic yogurt sauce and enjoy! ⁣

Syrian Eats - Macarona b Laban 🧄 This heavenly pasta is creamy, garlicky, nutty, and absolutely delicious. I grew up eating this and it never gets old! Find the written recipe below. Enjoy! ⬇️⬇️ #spicednice⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
🧄3 cups plain yogurt ⁣⁣
🧄1 tbsp crushed garlic⁣⁣
🧄1/4 cup water ⁣⁣
🧄Salt to taste⁣⁣
🧄Olive oil for cooking⁣⁣
🧄1 diced onion⁣⁣
🧄1 lb ground beef⁣⁣
🧄2 tsp allspice ⁣⁣
🧄1 tsp black pepper⁣⁣
🧄Salt to taste ⁣⁣
🧄1 lb pasta ⁣⁣
🧄3/4 cup toasted pine nuts in olive oil ⁣⁣
🧄1/2 bunch chopped parsley⁣⁣
🧄sumac ⁣⁣
🧄Aleppo pepper⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1. Mix the plain yogurt, crushed garlic, water, and salt to taste for the sauce and set aside. Boil the pasta until al dente. Sauté the diced onion in olive oil then add in the ground beef. Season with allspice, black pepper, and salt and break it up finely until cooked through. In a separate skillet, toast some pine nuts in olive oil until they turn golden. ⁣⁣
2. Begin to layer: first the cooked pasta, then the garlic yogurt sauce, then ground beef, then the toasted pine nuts, chopped parsley, and finally a sprinkle of sumac and Aleppo pepper. Enjoy!

node.text: Palestinian Food - Msakhan 🇵🇸 A traditional Palestinian dish that is so loved all over the Middle East. You can find this recipe in my Highlights under “Msakhan 2 ways” the first recipe in that highlight is the shortcut, sandwich version, and the second recipe in the highlight is this traditional version. Please continue praying and spreading the word about our beautiful brothers and sisters in Palestine. 💗🙏🏼🇵🇸

YALANGI 🙌🏼☘️ Tangy, incredibly flavorful vegetarian grape leaves. These are SO good and it’s almost impossible to eat just one! Find the written recipe below, enjoy 😊 #spicednice ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Filling: ⁣⁣
🍋1/4 cup olive oil ⁣⁣
🍋1 onion, diced ⁣⁣
🍋1 tbsp crushed garlic ⁣⁣
🍋1/4 tsp allspice⁣⁣
🍋3/4 tsp black pepper⁣⁣
🍋1 tsp seven spice⁣⁣
🍋2 tbsp dried mint⁣⁣
🍋Salt to taste (I used 1 tbsp) ⁣⁣
🍋1/2 tbsp red pepper paste⁣⁣
🍋1 cup finely diced tomato ⁣⁣
🍋3 cups Egyptian rice ⁣⁣
🍋1/3 cup lemon juice ⁣⁣
🍋1/4 cup pomegranate molasses ⁣⁣
🍋2 tbsp olive oil ⁣⁣
🍋1/2 cup finely chopped parsley ⁣⁣
To cook:⁣⁣
🍋1 jar grape leaves (about 75 grape leaves) ⁣⁣
🍋4 peeled potatoes, sliced into 1 inch disks⁣⁣
🍋Remaining juice from the rice filling ⁣⁣
🍋1 cup lemon juice (this makes them pretty tangy so feel free to add less (or more) to taste!)⁣⁣
🍋1/4 cup olive oil ⁣⁣
🍋1 tbsp salt (or to taste) ⁣⁣
🍋4.5 cups water ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
1. Soak the rice in water for an hour. Prepare the filling by heating 1/4 cup olive oil in a pan, then sauté the diced onion until it starts to soften. Add in the crushed garlic, allspice, black pepper, seven spice, dried mint, and salt then sauté it all for about 2 minutes. Add in the red pepper paste and toast for another minute then stir in the diced tomatoes. Turn off the heat now, then pour in the strained rice, lemon juice, pomegranate molasses, olive oil, and chopped parsley. Stir, then your filling is ready. ⁣⁣
2. If using jarred grape leaves, rinse them well then soak them in water for about 1 hour, then thoroughly rinse again to remove any excess saltiness from the brine. Cut off any thick stem then place the rougher side of the leaf facing upwards and add the filling to that side. Tightly fold the bottom of the leaf over the filling, then tightly fold both sides in, then roll it up as demonstrated in the video.⁣
